Gets Source File Name for Element

Source: R/DM_Server.R
DM_fetch_source.Rd

Gets file information about the current element

Usage

DM_fetch_source(state, element)

Arguments

state

DM state from DM_fetch_state()

element

Element list from DM_fetch_current_element()

Value

list with the following elements

  • isgood: Boolean indicating if the file is good (if it's an excel file and has a sheet).

  • msgs: Messages to be passed back to the user.

  • excel_file: Logical indicating if the source is an excel file.

  • excel_good: Logical indicating if the source is an excel file and we have a sheet defined in that file.

  • file_name: Base file name (e.g. 'file.csv')

  • full_path: Full path to the file (e.g. '/var/tmp/file.csv'), NULL if not found.

  • rel_path: Path to the file relative to user directory file (e.g. 'data/DM/file.csv'), NULL if not found.

  • sheet_found: Logical indicating if a sheet was found

  • sheet: Excel sheet selected by user

  • source_type: Type of source selected ("file", "url" or "unknown")

ele_ids =  names(state[["DM"]][["elements"]])
while(state[["DM"]][["current_element"]] %in% ele_ids){
  state =  suppressMessages(DM_del_current_element(state))
}

source_ids = sources_df$ID
for(source_id in source_ids){
  state = suppressMessages(DM_delete_source(state = state, id = source_id))
}
